WEBVTT

00:18.284 --> 00:19.451
(ellie)
previously on <i>gracepoint...</i>

00:19.453 --> 00:20.686
Lars pierson.

00:20.688 --> 00:22.054
His cell phone number
was found

00:22.056 --> 00:24.123
In the lining
of danny's jacket.

00:24.125 --> 00:26.959
I see you again,
I will lock you up.

00:26.961 --> 00:29.061
I'm pregnant.
We have to keep it.

00:29.063 --> 00:32.064
If the solanos need help,
they've got me to turn to.

00:32.066 --> 00:33.132
Shut your mouth.

00:33.134 --> 00:34.333
Get the hell
out of gracepoint.

00:34.335 --> 00:36.468
I know men
who'd rape you.

00:36.470 --> 00:38.003
Do you think
tom ran away?

00:38.005 --> 00:40.139
We have no idea
where he is.

00:40.141 --> 00:42.141
We've shifted our focus
to locating tom.

00:42.143 --> 00:43.342
Tommy!

00:43.344 --> 00:44.843
Tell me
about the boy.

00:44.845 --> 00:47.112
Answer...The question.

00:48.314 --> 00:50.215
Good lord.

00:53.486 --> 00:59.558
[dogs barking distantly]

01:03.663 --> 01:09.668
[soft background chatter]

01:09.670 --> 01:12.004
[wailing]

01:12.006 --> 01:15.407
Hey, it's okay, it's okay,
it's okay...

01:15.409 --> 01:18.177
.3 miles from the road
to the bike.

01:18.179 --> 01:20.379
.9 miles from the bike
to the cabin.

01:20.381 --> 01:21.914
<i>If he was here,</i>
<i>we would have found him.</i>

01:21.916 --> 01:23.348
<i>We have to go wider.</i>

01:23.350 --> 01:25.184
We have gone wider.

01:25.186 --> 01:27.186
We don't know
where he was taken.

01:27.188 --> 01:28.887
<i>He could be hurt</i>
<i>somewhere.</i>

01:28.889 --> 01:30.355
<i>[line breaking]</i>
<i>he could be cra...Ing</i>

01:30.357 --> 01:32.257
<i>..The woods.</i>
<i>Hello?</i>

01:32.259 --> 01:33.525
[sighs]

01:33.527 --> 01:36.195
Damn it.
I'm not
hearing you.

01:36.197 --> 01:38.197
Can you hear me now?
Better.

01:38.199 --> 01:40.466
Morgan says to wait
till dawn,

01:40.468 --> 01:41.733
But we've got
to do it now.

01:41.735 --> 01:43.035
<i>We cannot wait.</i>

01:43.037 --> 01:44.636
I think you should
go home, ellie.

01:44.638 --> 01:46.805
What?
<i>I think</i>
<i>morgan's right.</i>

01:46.807 --> 01:48.474
We'll expand
in the morning,

01:48.476 --> 01:50.309
Use the light,
bring more people in.

01:50.311 --> 01:53.212
You just
called me ellie.

01:56.049 --> 01:58.484
How can I leave
when he's still missing?

01:58.486 --> 01:59.885
People are looking.
You need rest.

01:59.887 --> 02:02.821
No, I'm coming
to you now,

02:02.823 --> 02:04.289
And we will get pierson
to talk.

02:04.291 --> 02:05.290
<i>I'm on pierson,</i>
<i>I promise.</i>

02:05.292 --> 02:06.825
I was just with him.

02:06.827 --> 02:08.560
I'll keep going back in
till he [static].

02:08.562 --> 02:10.629
Sir?
I cannot hear you.

02:10.631 --> 02:13.232
You are breaking up.
<i>[continues, garbled]</i>

02:13.234 --> 02:15.134
What?
I can't--hello?

02:16.436 --> 02:19.338
Damn it.

02:19.340 --> 02:22.341
Damn it!

02:22.343 --> 02:25.077
Hey.

02:25.079 --> 02:26.311
Hey.

02:26.313 --> 02:27.679
I just got off
with owen.

02:27.681 --> 02:30.282
Dylan is having
a rough time.

02:30.284 --> 02:32.284
He's--
he's not asleep?

02:32.286 --> 02:36.121
No, he never went down.
He wants his mama.

02:36.123 --> 02:38.257
Carver did just
tell me to leave.

02:38.259 --> 02:41.593
He is your boss.

02:41.595 --> 02:44.363
Yeah.
Go to dylan.

02:44.365 --> 02:47.199
He needs you.
I'll stay here.

02:47.201 --> 02:48.867
Okay.
Okay?

02:48.869 --> 02:50.202
Okay.

02:56.643 --> 02:58.944
<i>(girl)</i>
<i>a lot of us</i>
<i>are kind of scared.</i>

02:58.946 --> 03:01.480
<i>I mean, we know</i>
<i>we're probably safe,</i>

03:01.482 --> 03:03.115
<i>And we think</i>
<i>they're gonna find him.</i>

03:03.117 --> 03:04.616
Do you think
they're gonna find him?

03:08.121 --> 03:09.621
I'd ask what
you're doing here,

03:09.623 --> 03:11.623
But there's no need for that,
is there?

03:11.625 --> 03:14.793
I'm actually
looking for owen.

03:14.795 --> 03:16.628
Tried texting him,
calling.

03:16.630 --> 03:19.398
He isn't answering.
Go figure.

03:19.400 --> 03:21.300
I know he's close
with his aunt.

03:21.302 --> 03:22.968
I just wanted to say
I'm sorry,

03:22.970 --> 03:24.236
See if there's anything
I can do.

03:24.238 --> 03:25.971
You haven't done
enough already?

03:25.973 --> 03:27.839
That's not fair.
Really?

03:27.841 --> 03:30.542
Hounding an innocent man
until he takes his own life?

03:30.544 --> 03:33.178
Stirring up trouble when
the town's already suffering?

03:33.180 --> 03:35.914
The minute tom disappeared,
I knew you'd be back here.

03:35.916 --> 03:36.982
What an opportunity.

03:36.984 --> 03:39.251
One kid dead,
another missing.

03:39.253 --> 03:40.852
More reason
to slam the police,

03:40.854 --> 03:42.321
Claim some connection
to rosemont.

03:42.323 --> 03:44.656
It would've been wrong
of me not to.

03:44.658 --> 03:45.824
Detective carver
worked both cases,

03:45.826 --> 03:47.693
Each with multiple victims.

03:47.695 --> 03:51.230
You know as well as I do this
could be another serial killer.

03:51.232 --> 03:53.599
I want you
out of my office.

03:57.503 --> 03:59.071
Is owen
at the millers'?

04:03.776 --> 04:05.777
I hope they find tom.

04:15.021 --> 04:19.891
(paul)
â™ª holy, holy, holy

04:19.893 --> 04:24.730
â™ª though the darkness
hides thee â™ª

04:24.732 --> 04:28.367
â™ª though the eye
of a sinful man â™ª

04:28.369 --> 04:30.235
Tommy!

04:30.237 --> 04:33.038
<i>â™ª may not see</i>

04:33.040 --> 04:35.107
Hey, you ever go
camping with tommy?

04:35.109 --> 04:39.711
Uh, yeah, we took
one trip to sequoia.

04:39.713 --> 04:42.214
It was right before
dylan was born.

04:42.216 --> 04:43.915
You ever take danny?

04:43.917 --> 04:45.751
Oh, all the time.

04:45.753 --> 04:50.322
But last year, he went on that
overnight with Sunday school,

04:50.324 --> 04:52.090
And he got a massive
spider bite.

04:52.092 --> 04:53.825
Tom told us.

04:53.827 --> 04:56.061
Yeah, poor kid.

04:56.063 --> 04:58.230
He swelled like
somebody clocked him.

04:58.232 --> 05:00.065
He swore he'd never
do it again.

05:00.067 --> 05:03.302
[dogs barking distantly]

05:03.304 --> 05:06.071
(renee)
I'll take any bed
you've got,

05:06.073 --> 05:08.073
Preferably not next
to detective carver but--

05:08.075 --> 05:10.075
We're fully booked.

05:10.077 --> 05:12.144
There's been a lot
going on.

05:12.146 --> 05:14.246
I'm sure you've heard.

05:14.248 --> 05:15.681
I have heard.

05:15.683 --> 05:19.584
You might try the motor lodge
down on route 3.

05:19.586 --> 05:22.087
Maybe you'll have
better luck there.

05:22.089 --> 05:23.522
Good night.

05:34.801 --> 05:37.869
[phone vibrating]

05:54.687 --> 05:59.191
â™ª holy, holy, holy

05:59.193 --> 06:04.062
â™ª lord god almighty

06:04.064 --> 06:07.532
â™ª all thy work
shall praise thy name â™ª

06:07.534 --> 06:12.137
â™ª on earth
and sky and sea â™ª

06:12.139 --> 06:16.308
â™ª holy, holy, holy

06:16.310 --> 06:20.979
â™ª lord god almighty

06:20.981 --> 06:24.483
â™ª there is a sign
at the sight of thee â™ª

06:24.485 --> 06:26.551
[brush rustling]

06:33.693 --> 06:35.761
Tom?

06:37.997 --> 06:40.365
It's okay, tommy.

06:40.367 --> 06:43.268
If you're there,
come on out.

06:43.270 --> 06:46.671
[dark music]

06:46.673 --> 06:54.746
â™ª

07:10.196 --> 07:11.530
Up!
Wake up.

07:11.532 --> 07:13.265
Time to talk.

07:13.267 --> 07:15.867
Look at me.

07:15.869 --> 07:18.737
Why was tom miller found
near your property?

07:18.739 --> 07:20.138
[tiredly]
oh, who'd you find?

07:20.140 --> 07:22.274
Tom miller was found
a mile east

07:22.276 --> 07:24.109
Of your property
at 1:00 a.M. Tonight.

07:24.111 --> 07:25.644
Why?

07:25.646 --> 07:28.046
I don't know how to answer
any of these questions.

07:28.048 --> 07:31.116
You have been seen with
or in close proximity to

07:31.118 --> 07:33.785
Two boys from gracepoint
who have gone missing

07:33.787 --> 07:35.587
In the past six weeks.

07:35.589 --> 07:37.823
One of them is dead.

07:37.825 --> 07:40.492
The other, thankfully,
has been found.

07:40.494 --> 07:43.094
What's your connection
to them?

07:43.096 --> 07:46.832
What's your
connection to them?

07:46.834 --> 07:49.901
[siren wailing]

07:53.773 --> 07:56.475
Oh, tom.

07:56.477 --> 07:58.243
Are you okay?

07:58.245 --> 08:00.011
Oh, baby.

08:07.987 --> 08:12.090
Sweetheart, detective carver
here has a couple of questions

08:12.092 --> 08:14.125
That he needs to ask you.

08:14.127 --> 08:17.329
Are you feeling
up to that?

08:17.331 --> 08:19.164
Okay.

08:21.467 --> 08:23.335
How's your leg?

08:23.337 --> 08:25.270
They fix you up?

08:25.272 --> 08:28.340
It's not so bad.
I fell and cut it.

08:28.342 --> 08:30.375
Yeah, your mom
told me.

08:30.377 --> 08:32.944
She also told me
that you said

08:32.946 --> 08:37.315
You've never met
lars pierson.

08:37.317 --> 08:39.985
That true?
You've never met him?

08:39.987 --> 08:43.955
You ever spoken
to him?

08:43.957 --> 08:45.790
No.

08:45.792 --> 08:49.027
Has he ever tried
to contact you?

08:49.029 --> 08:50.795
No.

08:50.797 --> 08:53.164
So you were going
to his house...

08:53.166 --> 08:55.300
On your own.

08:55.302 --> 08:59.971
I got lost,
and it got dark.

08:59.973 --> 09:03.475
Sweetheart,
why did you go there?

09:03.477 --> 09:07.178
What were
you trying to do?

09:07.180 --> 09:09.481
I heard you
talking about him,

09:09.483 --> 09:11.550
So I checked
your work bag.

09:11.552 --> 09:16.054
I saw his name and his number,
so I looked him up.

09:20.826 --> 09:22.827
When was this?

09:22.829 --> 09:25.263
When you had
his picture.

09:25.265 --> 09:27.232
Looked him up where?

09:27.234 --> 09:29.768
Online.
On my computer.

09:29.770 --> 09:32.737
What were you planning to do
when you found him?

09:35.274 --> 09:37.776
I don't know.

09:37.778 --> 09:41.613
Why did you have
one of danny's crossword books

09:41.615 --> 09:43.915
In your backpack?

09:43.917 --> 09:46.184
He left it over
at our house last spring

09:46.186 --> 09:47.919
When he slept over.

09:47.921 --> 09:52.090
I keep it with me
to remember him.

09:52.092 --> 09:53.391
I just wanted
to find the person

09:53.393 --> 09:55.860
Who might've killed
my friend.

09:55.862 --> 09:59.064
I wanted
to show it to him.

09:59.066 --> 10:01.700
What would that
have done?

10:01.702 --> 10:04.703
I don't know.
Make him feel bad?

10:04.705 --> 10:07.906
Made him
tell the truth?

10:07.908 --> 10:10.041
I just wanted
to help solve the case,

10:10.043 --> 10:11.876
For danny.

10:11.878 --> 10:13.411
Also...

10:13.413 --> 10:15.280
Also what?

10:17.617 --> 10:20.051
I wanted my mom back.

10:38.738 --> 10:40.505
Detective carver.

10:40.507 --> 10:42.307
Mark, what you
still doing out?

10:42.309 --> 10:44.009
Did you get anything
from pierson?

10:44.011 --> 10:45.744
Not a lot.

10:45.746 --> 10:50.315
Do you think he had anything
to do with tom going missing?

10:50.317 --> 10:53.652
Well, do you think
he killed danny?

10:53.654 --> 10:55.787
I just don't want you wasting
your time on the wrong guy

10:55.789 --> 10:57.422
When, you know, the guy
that you're after

10:57.424 --> 11:00.258
Could be right
in front of us.

11:00.260 --> 11:03.261
Is there something specific
you want to tell me?

11:03.263 --> 11:04.663
Is it strange to you
that paul coates

11:04.665 --> 11:06.164
Found tom's bicycle,

11:06.166 --> 11:07.832
And then he's the one
who found tom

11:07.834 --> 11:09.601
Eight hours later?

11:09.603 --> 11:11.770
I mean, is it strange to you
that he takes every opportunity

11:11.772 --> 11:14.606
That he can get to put himself
in front of a camera?

11:14.608 --> 11:16.307
And I know that you're
probably gonna think

11:16.309 --> 11:18.276
That this is meaningless,
but is it strange to you

11:18.278 --> 11:19.711
That he's in love
with my wife,

11:19.713 --> 11:21.346
Has been
for the last 20 years,

11:21.348 --> 11:22.947
Ever since the beginning
of high school?

11:22.949 --> 11:24.949
That's not necessarily
meaningless.

11:24.951 --> 11:27.886
Because he hates that
me and beth are together.

11:27.888 --> 11:30.689
He hates
that we're a family.

11:30.691 --> 11:32.157
Okay.
There's--
there's one more

11:32.159 --> 11:34.225
Thing that
you should know.

11:34.227 --> 11:35.960
A client of mine saw him

11:35.962 --> 11:37.796
At a narcotics
anonymous meeting

11:37.798 --> 11:40.131
Over in winstead
last week.

11:40.133 --> 11:43.668
The minister
goes to n.A. Meetings?

11:43.670 --> 11:46.805
Might be worth
looking into.

11:46.807 --> 11:48.540
All right.

11:55.681 --> 11:57.182
You don't have to go,
you know.

11:57.184 --> 11:58.550
You can wait
if you want.

11:58.552 --> 12:01.419
Wait for what?
To get even more behind?

12:01.421 --> 12:02.887
I'm meeting jess
at the corner.

12:02.889 --> 12:04.823
She hasn't eaten.
I'm not hungry.

12:04.825 --> 12:06.758
Just have a piece
of toast or a banana.

12:06.760 --> 12:09.227
I'm fine.
I'll see you guys later.

12:09.229 --> 12:10.929
Bye, <i>mija.</i>
<i>Bye.</i>

12:10.931 --> 12:14.265
Want me
to pick you up?

12:14.267 --> 12:16.401
Well, guess
she's all right.

12:16.403 --> 12:18.503
God, I hope so.
Will you be?

12:18.505 --> 12:19.671
Back at work?

12:19.673 --> 12:21.339
I'm always all right.

12:21.341 --> 12:23.441
What are you gonna do?
Are you gonna go see your mom?

12:23.443 --> 12:25.543
I might to try
to reach ellie, actually,

12:25.545 --> 12:27.378
Tell her how happy
I am about tom.

12:27.380 --> 12:28.580
That's nice.

12:28.582 --> 12:31.783
Do you think so,
or is it...

12:31.785 --> 12:33.284
Is it what?

12:33.286 --> 12:36.221
I don't know.
I don't know what it is.

12:36.223 --> 12:38.089
<i>What's going on?</i>

12:40.025 --> 12:41.860
I don't know.
It's hard, mark.

12:41.862 --> 12:44.195
It's just so...

12:46.966 --> 12:48.800
They get him back.

12:48.802 --> 12:53.204
Oh, I know.
I know.

12:53.206 --> 12:55.974
I know.

12:55.976 --> 13:01.279
Well, it kind
of gave us a purpose...

13:01.281 --> 13:03.948
You know,
searching for him.

13:03.950 --> 13:07.051
We still don't know
what happened with danny.

13:09.421 --> 13:12.557
Have you thought
more about the baby?

13:16.262 --> 13:18.396
Have a good day
at work.

13:18.398 --> 13:20.665
Tell vince
I say hi.

13:30.609 --> 13:32.010
[sighs]

13:32.012 --> 13:34.245
Well,
he's finally sleeping.

13:36.015 --> 13:38.383
You look like you could use
some sleep yourself.

13:41.821 --> 13:44.088
Listen, emmett, um,
I just really wanted

13:44.090 --> 13:47.192
To thank you
for your concern

13:47.194 --> 13:48.426
And devotion
over these--

13:48.428 --> 13:50.361
Don't call me emmett.

13:50.363 --> 13:52.297
Why? You...

13:52.299 --> 13:54.299
Called me ellie
only a few hours ago.

13:54.301 --> 13:55.433
I shouldn't
have done that.

13:55.435 --> 13:58.002
Inappropriate.

13:58.004 --> 13:59.470
Did anyone ever
tell you

13:59.472 --> 14:02.340
You tend to run
a little hot and cold?

14:02.342 --> 14:04.609
No.
Really?

14:04.611 --> 14:06.211
I've heard
the cold part.

14:06.213 --> 14:08.446
You working today,
or you taking the day off?

14:08.448 --> 14:09.714
Well...

14:09.716 --> 14:12.317
Forensic analysis
from the burnt-out boat.

14:12.319 --> 14:14.185
Blood, hair,
and prints from danny.

14:14.187 --> 14:17.288
Paint chips match the color
of danny's skateboard.

14:17.290 --> 14:19.557
Why would they have danny's
skateboard on that boat?

14:19.559 --> 14:21.492
Traces of ammonia
from a glass cleaning product

14:21.494 --> 14:24.495
Matching with the product
also used on danny's body.

14:24.497 --> 14:26.631
The killer apparently tried
to wash off any evidence

14:26.633 --> 14:28.199
After moving him
down the coast.

14:28.201 --> 14:30.401
Using glass cleaner?
Did they--

14:30.403 --> 14:32.070
You think they found it
at the hut?

14:32.072 --> 14:34.372
Yeah. Grabbing
whatever was close.

14:34.374 --> 14:35.907
Stealing a boat
from the beach.

14:35.909 --> 14:39.010
They weren't prepared
for whatever happened there.

14:39.012 --> 14:41.980
Also I found out
something interesting

14:41.982 --> 14:44.916
About our local minister.

14:44.918 --> 14:47.552
You know he goes
to narcotics anonymous meetings?

14:47.554 --> 14:48.920
Paul coates does?

14:48.922 --> 14:52.590
Yeah, drives up north
all the way to winstead.

14:52.592 --> 14:54.826
Guess I'm
working today.

15:10.409 --> 15:11.876
Renee?

15:11.878 --> 15:14.846
Hi. What are you doing
sleeping in your car?

15:17.116 --> 15:20.118
[disorienting music]

15:20.120 --> 15:28.192
â™ª

15:40.639 --> 15:42.941
Lengthy theoretical
discussions,

15:42.943 --> 15:45.710
Each of which is built
around a recurring theme:

15:45.712 --> 15:49.547
Guilt, sin, isolation.

15:49.549 --> 15:51.482
<i>And when you're working</i>
<i>on your reports,</i>

15:51.484 --> 15:53.785
<i>I'd like you to focus on...</i>

15:53.787 --> 15:55.987
[voice fades]

15:59.825 --> 16:02.293
I wonder if I could
ask you a favor.

16:02.295 --> 16:03.494
Sure.

16:03.496 --> 16:05.797
You told me you were
still in touch

16:05.799 --> 16:07.999
With one of the mothers
from rosemont.

16:08.001 --> 16:12.603
Yeah, yeah, um...
Kate blanchard, nina's mom.

16:12.605 --> 16:14.405
We, uh, we actually got to be
pretty close.

16:14.407 --> 16:17.175
If she'd be willing,
I would--

16:17.177 --> 16:19.844
I would--I'd like
to talk to her.

16:19.846 --> 16:23.514
I just--I thought
it might help

16:23.516 --> 16:25.917
To talk to someone who knows
what I'm going through,

16:25.919 --> 16:31.723
Who knows what
happens to us now.

16:34.960 --> 16:36.361
Oh, man, I think
we're gonna have to

16:36.363 --> 16:37.829
Replace this whole thing.

16:37.831 --> 16:39.864
We should probably check
the other ones too, right?

16:39.866 --> 16:42.100
All right, I'll cut the water
and turn off the boiler.

16:53.212 --> 16:54.512
<i>You okay, bro?</i>

16:57.383 --> 16:58.683
<i>Hey, mark!</i>

